m4_define( `m4_post_date', `2010-08-30')m4_dnl
m4_define( `m4_post_title', `Web-Site Source-Code Now Available')m4_dnl
m4_include( `posttrans.m4')m4_dnl
m4_begin_post
<p>
I am sharing the source-code for this web-site as a <a
href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mercurial">Mercurial</a> repository
hosted on <a href="http://bitbucket.org/">BitBucket</a>. The repository
can be found at <a
href="http://bitbucket.org/rmathew/website">bitbucket.org/rmathew/website</a>.
The source-code uses the <a
href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M4_%28computer_language%29"><tt>m4</tt></a>
macro processor for generating the content. It also uses <a
href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Make_%28software%29"><tt>make</tt></a>
and a few helper scripts for managing dependencies. It heavily depends
on the availability of a UNIX-like environment, as provided by Linux for
example.
m4_begin_post_rest
<p>
To create or update the information about the dependencies among the
source-files (stored in &ldquo;<tt>deps.mk</tt>&rdquo; and included by
the <tt>Makefile</tt>), run &ldquo;<tt>make deps</tt>&rdquo;. To generate
the content, run &ldquo;<tt>make all</tt>&rdquo;. The content is
generated in the &ldquo;<tt>pub</tt>&rdquo; folder. The source for the
content is in the &ldquo;<tt>src</tt>&rdquo; folder, while the
&ldquo;<tt>bin</tt>&rdquo; folder contains some helper scripts.
m4_end_post_rest
m4_end_post
